============================================================================
MainLayout.razor

Purpose: Main layout wrapper for all pages in the application
Every page uses this layout unless explicitly specified otherwise

Structure:
- @Body directive: Placeholder where page content is rendered
- Error UI: Displays when unhandled errors occur in components

How it works:
1. RouteView in Routes.razor specifies this as DefaultLayout
2. When page loads, @Body is replaced with page content
3. Layout provides consistent structure across all pages
4. Error UI appears at bottom of screen when Blazor encounters errors

Note: This layout is minimal - no navigation/header/footer
All UI structure is handled within page components (Home.razor)
============================================================================
